This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring August 26, 2012, as Women's Equality Day. The proclamation commemorates the 92nd anniversary of the 19th Amendment to the United States Constitution, which granted women the right to vote. It highlights the progress made in advancing women's rights and emphasizes the need to continue working towards gender equality. The proclamation also acknowledges the achievements of women in various fields, such as business, medicine, and the military. It calls upon the people of the United States to celebrate the accomplishments of women and recommit to achieving gender equality.